text: Olympiacos S.C. is the men's volleyball team of the major Greek multi-sport club Olympiacos CFP, based in Piraeus. It was founded in 1926 and has won two CEV Cups, a record 32 Greek Volley League Championships, a record 17 Greek Cups, 3 Greek Super Cups, a record 7 Greek League Cups and a record 14 Doubles. Olympiacos is ranked among the top European volleyball clubs. From the early 1990s to the mid 2000s they played in 11 European Final Fours and reached six European Finals. == Other websites == * Olympiacos Volleyball section web site www.olympiacossfp.gr Category:Volleyball clubs Category:1926 establishments in Greece Category:Sports organizations of Greece
